title: For Sale:  I guess common courtesy does not exist among our community of shooters
location: St Charles MO, St. Louis, Missouri
postcontent:
Well once again people are letting their tempers get the best of them. I posted some ammo for sale and this guy is acting like I am burning the american flag. Here is his dictated response to me and our conversation. (starts at the bottom with him responding to my ad)

Ive fought for the Bill of Rights and am still fighting so I can give you my opinion!!!! You suck!!!!! Walmart hasnt raised their prices but .90 a box. You guys stand there and wait and by it up taking anyone elses opportunity and then gouge it!!!!! Supply and demand is because of thousands of assholes like you. You might as well be in the white house as well!!!! Again SHAME on you!!!!

Sent from my iPhone

Me: Yeah Yeah, Shame on me and everyone else who is doing it. I'm not forcing anyone to buy it from me. 

Right now it is supply and demand. There is a shortage and it is not available. I have an available supply for a price that reflects the demand.  I have been trading and selling on here for the last year and have so with the most respect. 

You responded to my ad. If you don't want to buy it that is fine, but I don't need your opinions. Keep your thoughts to yourself please.

Open your eyes and see what is going on. It is much bigger than just me selling some ammo for profit. 

Thanks,


Message from: midwestmayhem@charter.net 

Message regarding: 600 rounds of .223 & 700 rounds of 9mm for sale

Him: Straight out of Walmart $7.97 & $21.97 per box. Shame on you!!!!! You are not helping whats happening!!!!!

Now I have been selling and trading on here for the last year and have met lots of good people and made lots of friends. I always try to be respectful even when I disagree with others and understand people are entitled to their opinions even when they are not asked for, but for someone to use profanity and carry themselves in this manner in my opinion is giving our community of friendly shooters a bad name. Please keep an eye out for this guy and hopefully no one else has to be treated like this. 

As always happy hunting and be safe. 

Thanks.

postcontent:
This is the Mossberg 500AB. The 500AB is the 500A Mossberg shotgun with some upgrades......specifically a Walnut stock VS. the various hardwood stocks found on the regular 500A model. This 500AB also has some metal etchings ,as seen in 1 photo, that the 500A doesnt have ...and it has a 30" barrel. (Every part on this 500AB is interchangeable with the regular 500A).
This is a fixed full choke 30" barreled shotgun. 30 inches is a long range shotgun. Perfect for Deer and Water Fowl...and predators of any nature. You get the 75-100 yard reach of a rifle, with the spread pattern of a shotgun. Full choke means it keeps it's shot pattern tight over a long distance, so you get killing/stopping power at rifle like distances. It functions flawlessly and it looks good. It isn't perfect in appearance, the blueing and the wood show some wear, but it looks good. The bore is beautiful inside...slick as a whistle. It also has a metal safety switch, not a plastic one like the newer Mossbergs. I love this shotgun, and the new owner will too. It has the weaver/picatinny scope mounts already on it. If you have a scope with weaver/picatinny rings, it will mount right up to the shotgun. I will trade this gun.

The Modular Sleep System (MSS) is a modular sleeping bag used by the United States armed forces.

The MSS consists of a camouflaged, waterproof, breathable Gore-Tex bivy cover, a lightweight patrol sleeping bag, and an intermediate cold weather sleeping bag. Compression sacks are included to store and carry the system. The MSS is available in colors compatible with the universal camouflage pattern. The patrol bag provides cold weather protection from 35 to 50 degrees Fahrenheit. The intermediate bag provides cold weather protection from minus 5 to 35 degrees Fahrenheit. Together, the patrol bag and intermediate bags provide extreme cold weather protection in temperatures as low as minus 30 degrees Fahrenheit. The bivy cover can be used with each of three MSS configurations (patrol, intermediate, or combined) to be comparable with the environment in which the system is being used; the bivy cover provides environmental protection from wind and water. Sleeping bags are made of ripstop nylon fabrics and continuous filament polyester insulation; camouflage bivy cover is made with waterproof, breathable, coated or laminated nylon fabric called Gore-Tex; the compression sacks are made with water-resistant, durable nylon fabric.

I bought bricks of 22lr last week for $18 bucks , still double what I paid years ago for the federal 550 bulk bonus packs ( 8.99 )  LoL . but a bargin . I can understand some guns going up , but 2500 for a 750 Ar ?  2000 for a 650 mini ? 

I'll give you the 2x on the mags , I'd be skeeeered too if I didn't have a few ( remember what they taught some of us in boy scouts ? BE PREPARED )

Hopefully the magazine Mfg's are in super high gear / overtime , and can get caught up with the supply before / if anything goes onto the books .

My local shop I'd be faithful to finally turned to the dark side on me last week . Won't say any names , but went from selling trade in's with the 3 mags down to 1 mag . Stay safe and be nice to your brother / neighbor !
